doc.after: Lake Winnipesaukee is the largest lake in New Hampshire. It is approximately 21 miles (34 km) long (northwest-southeast) and from one to nine miles (1.6 to 15 km) wide (northeast-southwest), covering 69 square miles (180 kmÂ²) (71 square miles when Paugus Bay is included),[1] with a maximum depth of 212 feet (64.6 meters).
